ANC Secretary General Gwede Mantashe says structures of the party are now allowed to discuss the names of leaders they want. JOHANNESBURG ANC Secretary General Gwede Mantashe says the NEC has proposed that the party's structures be allowed to discuss names of leaders they support for the leadership race.Mantashe briefed the media yesterday about the NEC meeting underway at the Saint George's Hotel in Pretoria.While the party hasn't opened its succession debate yet, some ANC leaders are already on a campaign trail.The secretary general says structures of the party are now allowed to discuss the names of leaders they want. We are not opening the contestation but we are going to phase two. Phase two is not nomination but allowing structures of the ANC to discuss names and link the name to the principles, but the nominations will be in September. 